news.title: How Raheja’s Leela Sky Villas stands out as a branded residency and redefines the idea of a luxury home
news.para: One such destination that has changed the face of this market in India is The Leela Sky Villas- Navin Minar in New Delhi. As the first managed residence branded by a 5-star hotel chain, The Leela Lace Holdings, in the city, it brings a slew of super luxurious amenities to those who want a lifestyle that reflects their success and showcases their accomplishments in life.

news.title: Country Garden's entire offshore debt to be in default if Oct 17 payment not made
news.para: Lack of payment - which is expected after Country Garden last week warned about its inability to meet offshore debt obligations - would make the firm the latest in scores of Chinese developers who have defaulted.

news.title: Maruti leases 270,000 sq ft at Tag Avenue in Gurugram
news.para: Haryana Chief Minister Manohar Lal Khattar had last year requested that the automobile giant shift its corporate office to Gurgaon while allotting 900 acres of land to Maruti Suzuki India Limited and Suzuki Two Wheeler India Private Limited in Haryana.

news.title: Noida authority demolishes 50 farmhouses on Yamuna floodplains, more to follow
news.para: Officials said that these farmhouses covered several acres, and the owners had erected concrete structures on their premises and ran commercial activities out of them.

news.title: Bengaluru: KSPCB collects Rs 4 crore of NGT's Rs 200 crore fine from apartments
news.para: ​Tasked with collecting the fine from builders or resident welfare associations, Karnataka State Pollution Control Board has collected only Rs 4 crore.

news.title: Mumbai: Railways yet to part with 47 acres for phase 1 of Dharavi rehabilitation
news.para: The railway land abuts Dharavi and is to be used for construction of phase I permanent accommodation. It was learnt that the physical survey of the land had been completed and discussions were on with the railways for its handover.

news.title: WeWork names David Tolley as CEO to boost turnaround efforts
news.para: Tolley, who was CFO of satellite operator Intelsat from 2019 to 2022, has been a WeWork board member since February 2023 and was interim CEO since May 2023.

news.title: Grasim industries to raise Rs 4,000 crore through rights issue
news.para: The proposed rights issuance by Grasim industries aims to fund the ongoing capital expenditure plan, repay existing borrowings, and support general corporate purposes.

news.title: UP-RERA issues show cause notice to two promoters in violation of advertisement rules
news.para: ORO Infra Developers LLP had released advertisement of ORO Constella and AIS Developers LLP had released advertisement of The Galleria in print publications.

news.title: Bengaluru: Mahadevapura residents rejoice after getting khatas
news.para: Those owning plots and flats in Mahadevapura zone were handed over A-khata certificates over the past week after the civic agency received complaints from hundreds of residents.

news.title: NCLAT suspends its judgement in Finolex Cable matter after Supreme Court's order for enquiry
news.para: The order was related to the annual general meeting (AGM) of Finolex Cables and Prakash Chhabria and Deepak Chhabria's legal tussle over the management control of the company.

news.title: Scrap policy on need-based changes: Chandigarh residents
news.para: The agenda of the meeting was to bring to the notice of UT administration the need-based regularisation policy implemented on January 3 this year.

news.title: Dalmia Bharat's net profit up 161% in Q2 FY24
news.para: Dalmia Bharat's total income stood at Rs 3,234 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 7.55 per cent from Rs 3,007 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Emaar India to invest $1.85 billion in two years: CEO ​Kalyan Chakrabarti
news.para: ​The firm intends to release around 10 million square feet of real estate over the next two years, expanding its presence into key markets including Mumbai, Pune, Bengaluru, and Hyderabad.

news.title: Cement industry struggles to compete in oversees markets
news.para: ​The industry body has demanded a reciprocal import duty, along with a correction in the inverted duty structure. ET has seen a copy of its letter to the ministry.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body goes slow on property tax recovery
news.para: ​Additionally, the employees have slowed down their property tax recovery drive as earlier it planned to send the notices for the recovery of dues, but now they would send SMS to the defaulters.
